pective terms, except as such enforceability may be limited by any applicable bankruptcy, insolvency, moratorium or similar laws affecting creditors' rights generally. (b) Upon the effectiveness of this Amendment, each Borrower hereby reaffirms all covenants, representations and warranties made in the Loan Agreement to the extent the same are not amended hereby and agrees that all such covenants, representations and warranties shall be deemed to have been remade as of the effective date of this Amendment. (c) No Event of Default or Default has occurred and is continuing or would exist after giving effect to this Amendment. (d) No Borrower has any defense, counterclaim or offset with respect to the Loan Agreement. 8
