  (d)           Disagreement.  If the Parties disagree as to the scope of Sellers obligations, or Buyer alleges a material breach by Seller of Sellers obligations, under Sections 5.2(b) or 5.2(c) above, the Parties shall jointly appoint a Neutral Expert to resolve the disagreement within five (5) days after a written request of either Party stating the scope of the disagreement or establishing the grounds of an alleged material breach.  A Neutral Expert is a licensed and practicing attorney with at least ten (10) years of experience as an environmental attorney in Pennsylvania, who shall not have been employed by either Party during the last five (5) years.  The Neutral Experts determination shall be final and binding and subject to no rights of appeal.
 
