8.10         
NOTICE OF ADVERSE EVENT OR NON-COMPLIANCE.
Borrowers shall notify Agent in writing as soon as possible and in any event within ten (10) days of obtaining knowledge of (a) any failure by any Borrower or any Third Party to comply with any provision of any Transaction Document, and (b) any event or occurrence which has or would reasonably be expected to have a Material Adverse Effect on any Borrower, any Borrower's business or any Borrower's ability to comply with any provision of any Transaction Document.
8.11         
COMPLIANCE WITH ENVIRONMENTAL LAWS.
(a)           Borrowers shall comply with all applicable Environmental Laws except where the failure to so comply would not cause a Material Adverse Effect on a Borrower.
(b)           Borrowers shall not cause or permit the unlawful Disposal of Hazardous Substances at any property owned, leased or operated by them or any Consolidated Subsidiary.
