Section 5  CORPORATE GOVERNANCE AND MANAGEMENT
On February 5, 2009, the Board of Directors of Air Methods Corporation, a Delaware corporation (the ), adopted the Economic Value Added Bonus Plan (the ).  Under the Plan, certain executive officers of the Company (each, a  and collectively, the ) are eligible to receive incentive compensation based upon the financial performance of the Company during the Performance Period (as defined below).  The Compensation Committee (the ) of the Board of Directors shall administer the Plan and calculate all amounts to which the participants are entitled thereunder.  The Participants include Michael D. Allen, Trent J. Carman, David L. Dolstein, Paul Tate and Aaron D. Todd.  All capitalized terms that are not otherwise defined herein shall have the meaning ascribed to such terms under the Plan.
