(g)           Except as set forth in Section 6.10(g) of the Company Disclosure Schedule, all Tax allocation, Tax sharing, Tax indemnity or similar agreements between the Company or any of its Subsidiaries and any other Person shall be terminated with respect to the Company and each of its Subsidiaries prior to the Closing Date.  After the Closing Date neither the Surviving Corporation nor any of its Subsidiaries shall be bound by or have any further Liability or obligation under any such agreement.
 
(h)           The parties hereto agree to treat the transactions contemplated by this Agreement as a taxable purchase and sale of the stock of the Company for all U.S. federal and, where possible, applicable state income Tax purposes, to report the transactions as such for all such Tax purposes, and to take no action inconsistent with such treatment.
 
