This AMENDED AND RESTATED REVOLVING CREDIT, TERM LOAN AND SECURITY AGREEMENT (this "Agreement"), dated as of July 5, 2011, is by and among AIR METHODS CORPORATION, a Delaware corporation ("AMC"), ROCKY MOUNTAIN HOLDINGS, L.L.C., a Delaware limited liability company ("RMH"), MERCY AIR SERVICE, INC., a California corporation ("Mercy"), LIFENET, INC., a Missouri corporation ("Lifenet"), FSS AIRHOLDINGS, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("FSS"), CJ SYSTEMS AVIATION GROUP, INC., a Pennsylvania corporation ("CJ Systems"),AIR METHODS TRANSPORT COMPANY, a Delaware corporation ("AMTC"), UNITED ROTORCRAFT SOLUTIONS, LLC, a Texas limited liability company ("URS"), and SPECIAL JET SERVICES, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("SJS")as borrowers and debtors (together with the other borrowers which are or become a party hereto each individually, a "Borrower" and collectively, the "Borrowers"), KEYBANK NATIONAL ASSOCIATION, a national banking association, as a Lender, as lead arranger, sole book runner and administrative agent (KeyBank" or "Agent"), PNC BANK, National Association, as a Lender, as Joint Lead Arranger and Documentation Agent,  BBVA COMPASS BANK, as a Lender, as Joint Lead Arranger and Co-Syndication Agent, BANK OF AMERICA, N.A., as a Lender, as Joint Lead Arranger and Co-Syndication Agent and the other LENDERS (as hereinafter defined).
 
 
A.           AMC, RMH, Mercy, Lifenet, FSS, CJ Systems, AMTC and URS (the "Existing Borrowers") are parties to that certain Revolving Credit, Term Loan and Security Agreement dated as of September 17, 2007, as amended by Joinder and Amendment No. 1 to Revolving Credit, Term Loan and Security Agreement dated as of October 1, 2007, Amendment No. 2 to Revolving Credit, Term Loan and Security Agreement dated as of July 30, 2008, Amendment No. 3 to Revolving Credit, Term Loan and Security Agreement dated as of March 31, 2009, Joinder and Amendment No. 4 to Revolving Credit, Term Loan and Security Agreement dated as of May 14, 2010 and Amendment No. 5 to Revolving Credit, Term Loan and Security Agreement dated as of March 31, 2011 (said Loan and Security Agreement, as the same was amended from time to time, is hereinafter referred to as the "Original Loan Agreement").
B.           SJS is a wholly owned subsidiary of FSS and a guarantor of the obligations of the Existing Borrowers under the Original Loan Agreement.
C.           The Existing Borrowers and SJS have requested that KeyBank act as Agent to provide an increased revolving credit facility pursuant to which the Lenders will provide funding to Borrowers in an aggregate principal amount equal to the Total Revolving Credit Commitment (the "Revolving Facility") and an increased term facility in an aggregate principal amount equal to the Term Loan Amount (the "Term Facility") to finance AMC's acquisition of OF Air Holdings Corporation, a Delaware corporation ("OF Target") and provide for the working capital needs of the Borrowers as described herein, and KeyBank has agreed to act as Agent for the Lenders to provide such increased credit facility.
 
