"Solvent" means as to any Person, that such Person (i) owns assets whose fair saleable value is greater than the amount required to pay all of such Persons Consolidated Debt (including contingent debts), (ii) is able to pay all of its Consolidated Debt as such Consolidated Debt matures and (iii) has capital sufficient to carry on its business and transactions and all business and transactions in which it is about to engage.  In determining whether a Person is Solvent, all rights of contribution of each Borrower and Consolidated Subsidiary against other Borrowers and Consolidated Subsidiaries under any Transaction Document relating to the Obligations, at law, in equity or otherwise shall be taken into account.
