"Total Adjusted Debt" means, with respect to the Borrowers and their Consolidated Subsidiaries at any date of computation, the sum of (i) all Consolidated Debt, less(ii) short term notes payable secured by assets held for sale, plus (iii) the product of six (6) times (A) all Recurring Rents paid by such persons during the four (4) Fiscal Quarters ending with the date of computation plus (B) any unfavorable lease amortization.
 
