11.           .  Executive agrees that the covenants set forth in Sections 6 through 10 are reasonable with respect to their duration, geographical area and scope.  In the event that any of the provisions of Sections 6 through 10 relating to the geographic or temporal scope of the covenants contained therein or the nature of the business or activities restricted thereby shall be declared by a court of competent jurisdiction to exceed the maximum restrictiveness such court deems enforceable, such provision shall be deemed to be replaced herein by the maximum restriction deemed enforceable by such court.
Reasonableness of Restrictions
 
 
